The State of Ohio, Appellee, v. Buskey, Appellant.

[Cite as State v. Buskey (1996), 76 Ohio St.3d 23.]

(No. 95-1996 — Submitted June 5, 1996 — Decided July 3, 1996.) Michael Miller, Franklin County Prosecuting Attorney, and Katherine Press, Assistant Prosecuting Attorney, for appellee. Judith M. Stevenson, Franklin County Public Defender, and Paul Skendelas, Assistant Public Defender, for appellant.

The judgment of the court of appeals, upholding the constitutionality of R.C. 2925.03(M) and 4507.16(D)(2), is affirmed on the authority of State v. Thompkins (1996), 75 Ohio St.3d 558, 664 N.E.2d 926.

Moyer, C.J., Douglas, Resnick, F.E. Sweeney, Pfeifer, Cook and Stratton, JJ., concur.
